{{no footnotes|date=February 2013}}
The '''[[Kokkilai]] massacre''' was carried out by the [[Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam]].

== Incident ==
The [[Kokkilai]] village massacre is an incident on December 1, 1984, in which [[LTTE]] cadres [[massacre]]d 11 [[Sinhalese people|Sinhalese]] civilians. This attack occurred on the day after the  [[Kent and Dollar Farm massacres]]. Most of the victims were Sinhalese fishermen, were shot to death by LTTE cadres.

