{{Asiad infobox | Name = XX Summer Deaflympics | Logo = | Size = | Optional caption = | Motto = ''Melbourne in the World | Host city = [[Melbourne]], {{AUS}} | Nations participating = 82 countries | Athletes participating = 3,307 athletes | Events = 147 in 14 sports | Opening ceremony = 5 January | Closing ceremony = 16 January | Officially opened by = [[Marigold Southey]] | Torch lighter = | Stadium = [[Olympic Park, Melbourne]] |Website = [https://web.archive.org/web/20050206024223/http://2005deaflympics.com/ 2005deaflympics.com] |previous = [[2001 Summer Deaflympics|Rome 2001]] |next=[[2009 Summer Deaflympics|Taipei 2009]] |}}
The '''2005 Summer Deaflympics''', officially known as the '''20th Summer Deaflympics''', is an international [[multi-sport event]] that was celebrated from 5 January to 16 January 2005 in [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]].
==Bidding process==
A bid for the games was held on 9 March 1999 in Davos, Switzerland.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.deafsports.org.au/2005.htm |title=Melbourne wins 2005 Deaflympics |access-date=2001-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010805231031/http://www.deafsports.org.au/2005.htm |archive-date=2001-08-05 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.webbynation.com/davos/melbourne.html |title=Melbourne wins 2005 bid |access-date=2001-09-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010906014048/http://www.webbynation.com/davos/melbourne.html |archive-date=2001-09-06 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref> *[[Melbourne]], {{flag|Australia}} - 59 *[[Košice]], {{flag|Slovakia}} - 33
