{{Infobox football match | title = 2015 All-Ireland Senior Camogie Final | image = | event = [[2015 All-Ireland Senior Camogie Championship]] | team1 = [[Cork senior camogie team|Cork]] | team1association = [[File:Cork colours.PNG|40px]] | team1score = 1-13 | team2 = [[Galway senior camogie team|Galway]] | team2association = [[File:Galway colours.PNG|40px]] | team2score = 0-09 | details = | date = 13 September 2015 | stadium = [[Croke Park]] | city = [[Dublin]] | man_of_the_match1a = | referee = R Kelly (Kildare) | attendance = | weather = Dry | previous = [[2014 All-Ireland Senior Camogie Championship Final|2014]] | next =[[2016 All-Ireland Senior Camogie Championship Final|2016]] }} The '''2015 All-Ireland Senior Camogie Championship Final''' was the eighty-fourth All-Ireland Final and the deciding match of the [[2015 All-Ireland Senior Camogie Championship]], an inter-county [[camogie]] tournament for the top teams in [[Ireland]]. It took take place on Sunday 13 September in [[Croke Park]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.the42.ie/live-senior-camogie-final-cork-galway-2328311-Sep2015/|title=As it happened |date=14 September 2015|work=The 42|accessdate=15 September 2015}}</ref>
The match was shown live on ''[[RTÉ Two]]'' with commentary by [[Marty Morrissey]].
Cork won the title after a 1-13 to 0-9 victory against Galway.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/revamped-cork-make-transition-look-easy-353676.html|title=Revamped Cork make transition look easy|date=14 September 2015|work=Irish Examiner|accessdate=15 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gaa.ie/gaa-news-and-videos/daily-news/1/1409150758-camogie-cork-beat-galway-to-retain-senior-title/|title=LIBERTY INSURANCE ALL-IRELAND SENIOR CAMOGIE CHAMPIONSHIP FINAL: CORK 1-13 GALWAY 0-9|date=14 September 2015|work=GAA.ie|accessdate=15 September 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150916220742/http://www.gaa.ie/gaa-news-and-videos/daily-news/1/1409150758-camogie-cork-beat-galway-to-retain-senior-title|archivedate=16 September 2015|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.ie/sport/gaelic-games/camogie/thompson-and-cork-in-heaven-as-titles-stack-up-31523742.html|title= Thompson and Cork in ‘heaven’ as titles stack up|date=14 September 2015|work=Irish Independent|accessdate=15 September 2015}}</ref>
