{{Infobox NRHP | name = Cottrill Opera House | nrhp_type = | image = Cottrill Opera House Jul 06.jpg | caption = Cottrill Opera House, July 2006 | location= East Ave., [[Thomas, West Virginia]] | coordinates = {{coord|39|9|1|N|79|29|53|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = West Virginia#USA | built = 1902 | architect = [[Holmboe & Lafferty]] | architecture = | added = August 29, 1979 | area = {{convert|0.3|acre}} | governing_body = Private | refnum = 79002602 <ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2009a}}</ref> }} '''Cottrill Opera House''', known since 1915 as Sutton's Opera House or Sutton Theater, is a historic vaudeville and movie [[Theater (structure)|theater]] building in [[Thomas, West Virginia|Thomas]], [[Tucker County, West Virginia]]. It was built in 1902, and is a rectangular brick building with a high front that appears to be four stories tall. The interior is dominated by a large auditorium with balcony seating.<ref name="dhr">{{cite web|url=http://www.wvculture.org/shpo/nr/pdf/tucker/79002602.pdf|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory Nomination Form: Cottrill Opera House|date=April 1979|accessdate=2011-07-09 |author=James E. Harding|publisher=State of West Virginia, West Virginia Division of Culture and History, Historic Preservation}}</ref> The building is being restored for use as a live performance theater.
It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1979.<ref name="nris"/>
