[[File:1 Live Krone 2013 Johanna Klum 1.jpg|thumb]]
'''Johanna Klum''' (born 12 July 1980 in [[Berlin]]) is a [[Germany|German]] [[television presenter]] and former [[singer]].<!-- Unsourced image removed: [[Image:johanna.jpg]] -->

Johanna was a member of the German girl band ''Samajona'' until 2002, after which she became the presenter of [[Total Request Live]] on [[MTV]].

In 2005, she started working for [[Viva (TV station)|VIVA]], where she presented the show ''17'', now presenting the follow-up VIVA Live!, with her colleagues [[Gülcan Kamps]], [[Collien Fernandes]], and [[Klaas Heufer-Umlauf]].

In 2007, she presented the show ''Popstars-Das Magazin'', which referred to the sixth season of [[Popstars (Germany)|Popstars]] under the title ''Popstars on Stage''. The show aired on both VIVA and [[Pro7]], the original ''Popstars'' channel.

